  <!-- how it works -->
<div class=row>
  <h2 class="section-header center custom-header hiw-h" id="how-it-works">How it works</h2>
</div>

 <section id="cd-timeline" class="container how-it-works-block">
  <div class="cd-timeline-block">
    <div class="cd-timeline-img">
        <i class="fa fa-plus-circle fa-4x"></i>
    </div>

    <div class="cd-timeline-content">
      <h2>Create</h2>
      <p>Create a campaign for any upcoming NHL  game. Each campaign is unique, allowing the user to develop their own based on a particular hockey game, their favourite charity, or even their Twitter community.</p>
      <span class="cd-date"><h4 class="step">Step 1.</h4></span>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="cd-timeline-block">
    <div class="cd-timeline-img">
        <i class="fa fa-paper-plane fa-3x"></i>
    </div>

    <div class="cd-timeline-content">
      <h2>Share</h2>
      <p>Once created, a campaign summary email will be sent to the admin.  This can be shared with the creator's community, providing them with information and a link to the campaign.</p>
      <span class="cd-date"><h4 class="step">Step 2.</h4></span>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="cd-timeline-block">
    <div class="cd-timeline-img">
        <i class="fa fa-check-circle-o fa-4x"></i>
    </div>

    <div class="cd-timeline-content">
      <h2>Pledge</h2>
      <p>Before the game starts, users can create pledges based on <em>"In-Game Events"</em> such as goals, penalties, or shots saved by a particular player. A pledge is the dollar amount owed per occurrence of the selected in-game event.</p>
      <span class="cd-date"><h4 class="step">Step 3.</h4></span>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="cd-timeline-block">
    <div class="cd-timeline-img">
        <i class="fa fa-users fa-3x"></i>
    </div>

    <div class="cd-timeline-content">
      <h2>Watch</h2>
      <p>Watch the <em>"Game Feed"</em> display live in-game events, while the <em>"Leaderboard"</em> tracks all of the user's pledges. Users can check in on the live Twitter feed to keep up-to-date with the game and banter with friends. </p>
      <span class="cd-date"><h4 class="step">Step 4.</h4></span>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="cd-timeline-block">
    <div class="cd-timeline-img">
      <i class="fa fa-heart fa-4x "></i>
    </div>

    <div class="cd-timeline-content">
      <h2>Donate</h2>
      <p>Once the game ends, users can review the <em>"Pledge Board"</em> summary and head over to the charity website and donate.</p>
      <span class="cd-date"><h4 class="step">Step 5.</h4></span>
    </div>
  </div>

 </section>

